Asices] This word is applied to a simple game of the Romans, which is still very common among their descendants. The game is this. Of two persons, one, at a given signal, quickly opens any number of his fingers. At the same moment, the other endeavors to match his opponent by opening the same number. In the light, of course, each could see, as soon as it was done, whether the guess was successful. In the dark, hon- esty would be the only check to deception.
